    "keywords" -> {"linear algebra"}, "specialkeywords" -> {}, 
    "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True, "label" -> 
    "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "The first postulate indicates the mathematical description of the state \
of a system. Recall that in classical mechanics, the state of a particle in \
motion is described by the simple values of its position and momentum (or, \
equivalently, velocity). In quantum mechanics, the description is formulated \
at two different levels depending on the physical situation. See also Section \
1.1 of the Quantum Workbook (2022). Postulate 1. The quantum state of a \
closed system is completely described by a state vector in the Hilbert space \
associated with the system.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "Quantum States", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "", 
    "windowtitle" -> "Quantum States", "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
